## 🔧 **File 4: `setup.py`**

```python
from setuptools import setup, find_packages

setup(
    name="instaintel",
    version="2.0.0",
    author="Komal Butani",
    author_email="komal@example.com",
    description="Private ID Intelligence for Instagram",
    long_description=open("README.md").read(),
    long_description_content_type="text/markdown",
    url="https://github.com/ButaniKomal/InstaIntel",
    packages=find_packages(),
    install_requires=[
        'requests>=2.28.0',
        'colorama>=0.4.6',
        'pyfiglet>=0.8.post1',
    ],
    entry_points={
        'console_scripts': [
            'insta=insta:main',
        ],
    },
    classifiers=[
        "Programming Language :: Python :: 3",
        "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License",
        "Operating System :: OS Independent",
    ],
    python_requires='>=3.6',
)
